The number of frames per second can change dynamically depending on the content of the video. for example a video might be 60 fps during fast motion and drop to 15 fps during static scenes.

- Pros:
  - More efficient compression: fewer frames where nothing moves.
  - Can reduce file size while maintaining perceived quality.
- Cons:
  - Can cause audio sync problems in some editing software.
  - Not compatible with all platforms (some expect a consistent frame rate).
